thread.title: In New York City, Warehouses Have Nowhere to Go But Up

author: Keiko Morris
title: In New York City, Warehouses Have Nowhere to Go But Up
text:
In New York, an insatiable demand for warehouse space is colliding with a chronic land shortage. The only place for property developers to go is up.
At least two different development teams have unveiled designs for multistory warehouse projects, one in Brooklyn and the other in the Bronx, that would be the first of their kind in New York... To Read the Full Story Subscribe Sign In
